narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned a lot foundationally about these Regime types.

I learned about the difference between authoritarianism and totalitarianism as well as examples of authoritarian and totalitarian regimes in 20th century Europe, and emergent authoritarian regimes in the 20th century.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: It can be a little dry at times, but the discussions are usually worth it. I think diversity in the class structure and curriculum would help!
Readings were good, professor was good, essays were good- my only complaint is that the prof sometimes asks a lot of questions at once and I forget all of them.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, if youre willing to put in the work!
Yeah; its an interesting topic thats very relevant to the trends of democratic backsliding going on all over the world.
